    <IRS990ScheduleO documentId="RetDoc5">
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990 - ORGANIZATION'S MISSION</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE MISSION OF VESPER BOAT CLUB IS TO PERPETUATE ITS LEGACY OF DEVELOPING HIGHLY SKILLED AND COMPETITIVE ROWERS AT ALL LEVELS BY PROVIDING ITS DIVERSE COMMUNITY OF MEMBERS WITH PREMIER ROWING PROGRAMS AND FIRST-CLASS FACILITIES AND EQUIPMENT. THE CLUB MOTTO, ALL TOGETHER SYMBOLIZES AN ORGANIZATION OPEN TO ALL PEOPLE WHO WANT TO ROW, AND PROMOTES CHARACTER DEVELOPMENT AND PHYSICAL FITNESS THROUGH THE CHALLENGE OF THE SPORT.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PAGE 6, PART VI, LINE 6</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION HAS SEVEN CLASSES OF MEMBERSHIP AND PARTICIPATION: LIFE, HONORARY, FULL, THREE MONTH LIMITED, ASSOCIATE, SOCIAL, AND ALUMNI. ONLY LIFE AND FULL MEMBERS, WHO HAVE BEEN MEMBERS IN GOOD STANDING FOR AT LEAST TWO YEARS, ARE VOTING MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PAGE 6, PART VI, LINE 7A</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS CONSISTS OF NINE TO ELEVEN INDIVIDUALS: FOUR ARE ELECTED EACH YEAR BY VOTING MEMBERS FOR TWO YEAR TERMS. THE OFFICERS OF THE ORGANIZATION ARE ELECTED ANNUALLY BY VOTING MEMBERS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PAGE 6, PART VI, LINE 11B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE TREASURER AND THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD BEFORE FILING. ALL QUESTIONS AND COMMENTS TO FORM 990 ARE RETURNED TO FISCHER CUNNANE &amp; ASSOCIATES FOR EXPLANATION OR CLARIFICATION. SUBSEQUENT TO ALL QUESTIONS OR COMMENTS BEING ADDRESSED THE FINAL VERSION OF THE FORM 990 IS SIGNED BY MANAGEMENT AND SUBMITTED TO THE IRS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PAGE 6, PART VI, LINE 12C</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE STATEMENTS ARE COMPLETED AND RETURNED TO THE DESIGNATED OFFICER OF THE BOARD (TREASURER) WHO REVIEWS AND KEEPS THE STATEMENTS ON FILE. THE TREASURER NOTIFIES THE BOARD SHOULD ANY CONFLICT EXIST. THE BOARD WOULD THEN FOLLOW THE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST POLICY TO DETERMINE THE APPROPRIATE COURSE OF ACTION.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PAGE 6, PART VI, LINE 19</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
    </IRS990ScheduleO>
